      <a name="2" id="2"></a>
      <h3><a href="#2"><i class="fa fa-link"></i></a>How does Jackschess help me as a coach?</h3>
      <p>Jackschess will help you teach chess better online, and potentially get you more students.</p>
      <p>Nobody likes having to manage Skype/ICC or chess.com in the same screen, not to mention things like TeamViwer or programs that only Windows users can download. Group lessons are always a mess, you don't have all the features you need, etc. Skype and those websites aren't meant for a chess learning environment, Jackschess is. Jackschess isn't designed for multiple things, it is meant to create the perfect chess environemnt for players to connect and enjoy the game all over the internet.</p>
      <p>Jackschess also designed {{#link-to 'home.signup'}}accounts{{/link-to}} specifically for coaches. Having an account lets you have your own Jackschess room at your own personal URL. You also get a coaches toolbox where you can save positions, puzzles, games, recordings, etc. for later reuse in other lessons.</p>
