      <h3><a href="#4"><i class="fa fa-link"></i></a>What's the difference between a Jackschess room and a jackschess account?</h3>
      <p>Great question.</p>
      <p>A chess room is a place on the internet where you have video chat, a chess board, and a bunch of chess specific features all in one screen. It is hosted at a unique URL that you can share to invite whoever you want. However, a chess room is hosted at a random URL, anyone can join it, and you cannot save any data like positions, puzzles, games, etc.</p>
      <p>An account comes with your own profile to market yourself as a coach or student, and it comes with your own personal chess room. Your own chess room is hosted at a customized URL. For example my username is "JimmyMow", so my room is http://jackschess.com/jimmymow/room. Because I have an account that room is also protected by a password or what I call a "room secret", so that only the people you give your secret to can enter your room. Lastly, an account comes with a toolbox, which you can save positions, games, puzzles, lessons, etc to.</p>
